tags: work
title: Schoolboy Cruise '78
projectDate: 2007
description: >-
  A visual metaphor for the ego and the id of a 14 year old boy - myself in
  1978. The snapshots were taken on a school cruise which is also where the
  pornography was acquired.  At the time, the pornography seemed more
  interesting than the historical sights. It was the photographs that were shown
  on my return home, not the pornography. In this sense these pictures represent
  what we choose to show, juxtaposed with what we feel we cannot show. They also
  invite a questioning of how we view photographic images from distinct genres.




  This work was prefigured, by some 20 years, by a project documenting sculptural works produced in the mid 1980's. This project: *Excess* can be viewed [here](https://jonathanbaggaley.com/excess/).
